When Cunningham wanted to sell his house in 2003, he didn't bother to put it on the market. He said the sale price was based on ``comparables from an independent source'' -- but it turns out that source was a real estate agent whose family also has contributed heavily to Cunningham; Wade simply paid the asking price. Instead, according to reporting by Marcus Stern of Copley News Service, Cunningham -- who sits on the defense appropriations subcommittee -- turned to a defense contractor. 